name: RBC Target 2028 Canadian Government Bond ETF
longDescription: The fund investing primarily in a portfolio of fixed-income securities issued by Canadian governments and agencies that mature in the same calendar year as the ETFs termination date. RBC GAMs decision to invest in each Canadian government or agency bond is based on RBC GAMs assessment of each bonds term to maturity, credit quality, yield to maturity, issue size, liquidity, and an overall emphasis on issuer diversification. It is anticipated that the ETF will terminate on or about September 30, 2028. The ETF may invest no more than 20% of its assets in foreign securities. The investment objective of the RBC Target 228 Government Bond ETF is to provide income, for a limited period of time ending on the RBC Target 228 Government Bond ETFs Termination Date, by investing primarily in a portfolio of fixedincome securities issued by Canadian governments and agencies that mature in the same calendar year as the RBC Target 228 Government Bond ETFs Termination Date.
